<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 5:57PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL TIOGA COUNTY
THROUGH 630 PM EDT...
At 556 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mansfield, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Blossburg, Covington, Roseville and Mansfield University.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
north central Pennsylvania.</instruction>
